text:
the real definition of chivalry is jousting to the death. so it's been dead for quite some time. .
.
no more jokes because this subject really makes my spidey senses tingle (okay now officially no more jokes). this gillette ad is exposing so many people and i am living for it. it's not an attack on anyone unless you know you are guilty of it. why is it emasculating to be polite and respectful? .
.
i am empathetic to how men were raised. my brother was not allowed to cry because "boys don't cry" so i understand the confusion, but it's not excuse to try and understand and elevate your mindset. try to focus more on "how i can use what i was born with/ what i have to my benefit to help aid others". it's so simple and honestly so sexy. .
.
honestly, really think about it. why do you think women fall for doctors and firemen and superheroes? it's because they're selfless. they help others and allow themselves to be vulnerable. that's the fucking secret! #yourewelcome

text:
a long night waiting for updates from israel,  just one of many in this seemingly endless case. #article in #bio

at 2.30 am, the ministry of justice informed us that dr agav and dr vysbrod had both been cross examined about their reports that state leifer is fit to stand trial.
district psychiatrist, dr jacob charnes is expected to take the stand on the 24th of jan. dr charnes confirmed between 2014 - 2018 that leifer was unwell. when given the new reports that leifer was fit for trial, he delayed signing off on them and several court hearings were spent waiting for his signature. 
#trepidation #bringleiferback #2019is4justice
-
-

malka leifer, my former school principal is under custody in israel but is claiming mental illness in order to avoid extradition. news article link in bio. 
meanwhile in australia she has 74 charges of sexual assault to face and numerous victims waiting for a chance to face her in court. 
for more information on my campaign for justice visit my facebook page - dassi erlich; beyond a survivor  #supreme #court #courts #police #policeofficer #prison #jail #handcuffs #israel #israeli #jerusalem #justice #metoo #timesup #nomore #lookup #judge #religion

at 2.30 am, the ministry of justice informed us that dr agav and dr vysbrod had both been cross examined about their repos that state leifer is fit to stand trial.
district psychiatrist, dr jacob charnes is expected to take the stand on the 24th of jan. dr charnes confirmed between 2014 - 2018 that leifer was unwell. when given the new repos that leifer was fit for trial, he delayed signing off on them and several cou hearings were spent waiting for his signature. 
  019is4justice
-
-

malka leifer, my former school principal is under custody in israel but is claiming mental illness in order to avoid extradition. news aicle link in bio. 
meanwhile in australia she has 74 charges of sexual assault to face and numerous victims waiting for a chance to face her in cou. 
for more information on my campaign for justice visit my facebook page - dassi erlich; beyond a survivor

text:
so, you think the #metoo wave is over? that art therapy/ counseling is only relevant in crisis, a profession to cater to people who are "ill" in some way, shape or form? that it's "too intense" and you don't need to engage with things that aren't in the headlines?
:
:
i'm here to tell you there's no escape! #metoo will be alive as long as humanity will be alive; love, relationship, sexuality, power will be confusing because life is nuanced, deep, mysterious and confusingly beautiful. truth is beautiful, truth is mystical, and truth is power.
:
:
all these issues are relevant to all of us, we don't get to hide as long as we are alive. as i continue my second year of intensive trauma therapy with survivors of rape, abuse, harassment and all forms of sexual violence and my sixth year as an art therapist, i gain more insight through the pain i encounter in my everyday, in your everyday. here's an invite to an art therapy showcase i'm part of on jan 25th 2019, along with a bunch of amazing art therapists who explore similar questions in other settings within the field.
:
:
come, let's deconstruct some conditioning together. sending you sunlit skin and much power from the depths of a break i took in the lap of nature. â¤ï¸ #arttherapyaslivedinquiry #arttherapyispoliticalpersonal #artofconnection #workingwithsurvivors #traumatherapy #art #painting #mixedmedia #india #chicago #narratives #metoo #towardsatransformativeaccountability #health

text:
i know way too many people, women, men, girls, and boys, who have stories of their bodies being used like toys. too many people never stop to listen they would rather simply watch a television. but i am that girl and i know what it means to have a voice but never be seen. because no one will believe you or say it was wrong, they will blame you and tell you it's what you deserved all along. the fight is nowhere near over nor has it been won. it's 2019 and i feel afraid because what happened in high school will never go away, and it still happens to others every single day. coming together is the only way we will ever be heard, and telling our stories is the only way for us to ever hope to be cured. so please, if your voice has been silent or if you are still afraid i am here to tell you that it's time to stand up and say, enough is enough. change needs to come. so to every person who has a story like mine i beg you, i plead, raise your voices and fill your lungs because your story deserves to be sung. ~s

#truth #metoo #mystory #mytruth #sexualassualt #survivor #survivorstories #sexualassualtsurvivor #mine #poem #originalpoem #poetry #healing #beheard

text:
let me start out by saying that despite popular opinion from some men who have followed my story on social media - i love men!!
so here it goes...
speaking from lots and lots of experience in an area that i can be considered an expert...
when a man reacts with an unusual amount of anger or hate to an ad about men behaving like gentlemen, or in my case, when one of your male fb followers tells one of your close friends that, and i quote, â€œvickie doesnâ€™t like  men,â€ this typically means they have something in their past that they are ashamed, embarrassed, fearful, or guilty of as it pertains to their treatment of women, have been hurt emotionally by a woman, and/ or they have issues with their mother. and in my experience, if a woman has a similar reaction, then she is most likely involved with one of these men and isn't ready to see the truth. 
you donâ€™t have to like the commercials, by the products or follow me on fb. but to react with hostility or anger? well that sounds like some deep rooted issues that are bubbling up to the surface. 
men, this not a â€œwar on masculinityâ€!! trust me, we all love a strong manly man. but he is only considered a strong man if he treats all women  with respect, dignity, and sees her as his equal. 
i can't wait to get my book out into the world to offer a new perspective on a very universal and important issue. #vday2019*

as owners, of either #proctergamble stock or #gilette products, we should know what we own and hold companies accountable.

text:
congresswoman romero is another one of our speakers this saturday! angela romero has always had a passion to serve. growing up in tooele, utah, angela was raised by her grandparents. their dedication to raising a hard-working, well-educated woman inspired her to pursue college, graduating with a bachelorâ€™s degree in political science and a masterâ€™s degree in public administration from the university of utah. in 2012, she won election to represent house district 26 at the utah state legislature. in 2018, she was elected by her colleagues to serve as the house democratic assistant whip.
with almost two decades of public service, angela oversees community programs and initiatives in the division of youth and family programs, including supervising the youthcity government program. at the state legislature, she champions issues that include victimâ€™s rights, sexual assault and domestic violence prevention. in addition to her professional career and legislative duties, angela currently serves as the national hispanic caucus of state legislatorâ€™s vice president. she also serves on the prevent child abuse utah board of directors, utahâ€™s rape kit processing work group, friends for sight board of directors, salt lake acting company board of directors, and is the national foundation for women legislatorâ€™s utah state director. we are so excited to hear her speak!
.
.
.

text:
ğŸŒ·a few days in advanced, and i'm already thanking rev.dr. martin luther king jr. #mlk for his legacy that he has left us american citizens with to carry on! both morally and traditionally...
.
that most of us americans still remember and celebrate to this day.
.
i do, remember --as a kid, learning his legacy and how important it was to not just black-americans but all americans as well!
.
i do, remember -- being blessed with the opportunity to visit his gravesite as a kid in atlanta,georgia, and the loraine hotel in memphis, tennessee;  where he had his life taken from him in a abrupt and unjustly fashion.
.
but- we are all still, reminded to this day -- the greatness he has left for us to share, and the power of what could become of us, once we all started embracing and accepting one another with love! 
thank you #martinlutherkingjr for your major contribution in, for, and to society!

text:
toxic masculinityâ€¦ its a real issue.

donâ€™t think so? try reading this post without narrating justifications for your position as you read.

first, what is toxic masculinity?

to answer that clearly, let me start by defining what it isnâ€™t.

toxic masculinity is not making decisions in line with core values.
toxic masculinity is not hearing all sides of the story.
toxic masculinity is not allowing others to have their emotional experience.
toxic masculinity is not valuing women on the basis of their character, including their intellect, emotions, morals, purpose, and passions.
toxic masculinity is not allowing children to develop their own unique interests and build on their individual curiosities.
toxic masculinity is not giving others the space to be heard with understanding, empathy, and compassion.
toxic masculinity is not allowing others to have their opinions while deriving self worth on an internal basis of goals, ambitions, and successes of those goals.
and the list goes onâ€¦

as for what toxic masculinity is, well, rather than listing the inverse of all those items above, i leave you to parse that out for yourself given the context of the list. iâ€™m sure, if youâ€™re of a level of intelligence that doesnâ€™t immediately jump to a reaction, you also possess the capacity to ruminate the context of an â€œintegrated manhoodâ€œ. being the best a man can be involves being able to hear others, irrespective of if it bears any truth to the listener personally. stated another way, the reaction to the gillette commercial is indicative of exactly what the commercial is pointing out.

so what do i mean by â€œintegrated manhoodâ€. in simple terms, you have the ability to recognize, acknowledge, and address your emotional reality without making it someone elseâ€™s issue.

meaning, if you disagree with the gillette commercial, and you identify as per the male gender, do you have the capacity to allow a company to form their own marketing opinion while hearing them?

or do you feel a need to react? if you find conflict with the message, what are you doing with that internal position? how are you reconciling that in your experience? ...read the rest at my blog. link in bio.

text:
#gillette ğŸ‘Š
.
.
.
to anyone reading this (especially male)...if you don't know what the campaign is about this post will probably offend you. don't let it. the ad is not meant to target masculinity, but rather toxic masculinity (ie men who are aggressive towards women, men who objectify women, men who condone excessive violence, etc). it's intent is not to belittle men. but to hold men accountable for their actions and make us all think as a society. just because you're taught that fighting or cat calling women etc is ok, doesn't mean it is. be a free thinker and retrain your mind. masculinity is a very sexy and powerful thing. but like anything, in excess, it becomes unattractive.  as a woman i can tell you is is very uncomfortable to be looked up and down or cat called. it's awkward and upsetting. yet we raise our boys to think they have to be this way to fit in. nothing is sexier than when you see a man who has quiet confidence and is loyal and capable of showing some emotion alongside his strength. my dad was what i consider a real man. he was very masculine in ways. he was a hunter and fixed cars and could throw down in a fight when he absolutely needed to. etc. but he taught us to only fight as a last resort. he taught us compassion. we rescued so many animals i cant even begin to count. he wasn't afraid to cry when he would drop me off at the airport for school. he kind of personified that perfect blend of masculine strength and compassion and sensitivity. and let me tell you, he had the respect of the men in my hometown in spades. he was gentle and yet a so called man's man rip dad. and also the guy i'm currently dating sort of has that sexy blend of masculinity and sensitivity that i find so intoxicating. so to anyone reading this, it's not meant to degrade men.  i think we can all agree there are a lot of good, great men in this world. watch the ad and you'll understand. it's making a powerful and beautiful statement. men should be allowed to show emotions without being labeled "snowflakes" (in fact i find it so sexy when a guy can show emotions) and shouldn't be expected to fight and act like jerks.  thankfully society is changing. #compassion

text: in honour of aya maasarwe, i asked mum if tonight instead of driving to the cinema, if we could simply walk there and back. this is a basic human right that i should be allowed to walk freely at nighttime and feel safe. not once have i felt safe when walking alone at night, not once have i felt i could walk down the road instead of driving at night, not once have i felt i could walk after a night of drinking without needing a male to accompany me or needing a lift, not once have i felt safe to walk home from the station simply 10 minutes down the road at night, not once have i felt i could take my dog for a walk alone in the dark, not once. women should not have to be afraid to do a an activity such as walking home, without feeling like our lives may be at risk. we are not a convenience to men who see us at night, like an owl who sees their bait. we are humans, our lives are of just as much value as those of males. we are people, we have stories to tell and our stories are not, that we will continue to be treated as anything less than equals who deserve the same rights. as a man, you grow up feeling a sense of safety when alone; you are usually able to avoid being attacked, as men respect men. however, as females when alone, that be in daylight, but mostly night, we are at fear of being kidnaped, attacked, raped, murdered. itâ€™s been an injustice for too long. there should be no more antia cobyâ€™s, a nurse who was kidnaped, sexually assaulted and murdered for simply deciding to walk home alone after a dinner with colleagues. there should be no more jill meagherâ€™s, a married woman who decided to do the short walk from the bar home to her husband; but instead was kidnaped, raped, murdered and thrown in a ditch. there should be no more eurydice dixonâ€™s, who was kidnaped, raped and strangled while walking home, at only 22 years of age. there should be no more aya maasarweâ€™s who was getting off a tram near her home and on the phone to her sister; when she instead of walking inside and going to bed after watching a comedy show, was attacked and killed. this has to stop. these women canâ€™t die in vain. make change. be their voice.

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text_retweet:
#repost @hufilm1971 with @get_repost
ãƒ»ãƒ»ãƒ»
the students of howard university film and television program call for the establishment of a department of cinematic arts and television, effective fall 2019. howard has the most comprehensive film program, and offers the only mfa in film, of any hbcu in the united states. howard university has the only minority owned pbs affiliate in the nation. for decades since the founding of the film program in 1971, we have been fulfilling a national and global need for women storytellers and storytellers of color. still, there is no hbcu in the united states with a department dedicated to the study of cinematic arts and television - we can change this.

we are calling for the first department of cinematic arts and television, at any hbcu in the nation, to include the following components:

a) independently administered budget. 
b) independently managed equipment center and facilities. 
c) shared governance by the students and faculty over said budget, equipment center, curriculum development and implementation of the undergraduate and graduate bfa and mfa programs, as well as program and instructor evaluation. 
d) and a commitment to attract more of the most qualified professors in the industry, and to continue to produce graduates of the finest caliber.

support us by signing the petition, share the campaign with everyone you know, and let howard university president wayne a. i. frederick know that the time is now for a howard university department of cinematic arts and television.

why is this important?

since 1971, the howard university film program has produced and/or supported the most highly trained and widely acclaimed storytellers, including: bradford young, hans charles, ernest dickerson, arthur jafa, jenn nkiru, malik sayeed, alan ferguson, sehkar kammula, faraday okoro, lodi matsetela, lekgetho makola, nijla mumin, maori karmael holmes, floyd rance, yao ramesar, and shirikiana aina.

with the likes of stanley nelson, michelle parkerson, julie dash, and haile gerima having served as faculty in the program.

in the new era of #oscarssowhite, #timesup, and #metoo the film and television industry is clearing space to #tell
name: by Kimberly C. Gaines

text:
- what we worked on was ... data harvesting programs where we would pull data from users of apps and all of their friend networks and run that data through algorithms that could profile their personality traits and other psychological attributes, wylie told cnnâ€™s don lemon monday evening.

wylie said the ultimate goal was to obtain information in order to exploit mental vulnerabilities that our algorithms showed that [facebook users] had.

in addition to wylie and cambridge analytica, accounts of cambridge analyticaâ€™s parent company, strategic communication laboratories, and those of a university of cambridge psychologist aleksandr kogan were also suspended.

the accounts were suspended because facebook received reports that data that had been shared with cambridge and wylie from koganâ€™s app may not have been completely deleted. koganâ€™s app was removed in 2015 and facebook said they had been previously provided certifications that the data had been deleted. - several days ago, we received reports that, contrary to the certifications we were given, not all data was deleted, facebook said friday. - we are moving aggressively to determine the accuracy of these claims. if true, this is another unacceptable violation of trust and the commitments they made. we are suspending scl/cambridge analytica, wylie and kogan from facebook, pending further information.

special counsel robert mueller asked cambridge analytica last fall to surrender emails from any of its employees who worked for the trump campaign, the wall street journal reported in december. the firm complied to the request.

diana stancy correll
washington examiner

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election. - one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters
